        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 4:04PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 404 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles north of Greenville Downtown, or near Slater-Marietta, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Slater-Marietta, Tigerville, Table Rock State Park, Pleasant Ridge
State Park, Jones Gap State Park, Caesars Head State Park, Travelers
Rest, Lake Robinson, Pumpkintown, and Dacusville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
